with gross hematuria, and 1 patient with isolated upper gastrointestinal bleeding. Only 1 patient needed transfusion, a child with profound DSS who eventually made a good recovery. Liver enzyme abnormalities were relatively common but no patient developed jaundice or reported specific symptoms; in 1 patient the aspartate aminotransferase (AST) level increased to &#x0003e;1000&#x000a0;IU/L, but he remained stable and at follow-up liver function was entirely normal.
